      <bioghist>
         <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE </head>
         <p>Dr. Robert W. Kirk was born May 20, 1922 in Stamford, Connecticut. He received his B.S. from the University of Connecticut in 1943, and his DVM from Cornell University in 1946. He married Helen M. Grandish in 1949 and they have three children.</p>
         <p>Dr. Kirk's work in companion animal medicine is internationally recognized. He is perhaps best known for his text, 

		<title>Current Veterinary Therapy</title>, currently in its 13th edition.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent>
         <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
         <p>Correspondence, photographs, video cassettes related to Dr. Robert W. Kirk's career in veterinary medicine, including his writings as well as his work at the Cornell University Hospital for Animals at the Cornell University College of Veterinary Medicine.</p>
      </scopecontent>
